race.comment: SILVER AGENT (4) has only the one win from twelve starts and like the way he closed off when back in grade for a gritty second over 1920m at this track. At his top now and doesn't have to improve much to win this. JIMMY NAILS (2) comes off a 38-day let-up after pulling up lame at latest. Struggled to run the 3200m out when a poor eighth at the Gold Coast in a BM70. Blinkers go on and back to his preferred trip. Each-way. BORN TO BE ALIVE (9) first real blemish of the campaign when he failed to handle the firm surface with a tiring seventh over 2230m at Grafton. Gets weight relief and shapes as a value prospect. MISHANI REACTOR (1) back in grade when a commanding win as fav over 1600m at Thangool. Gets map favours with the claim.
